VideoCrumb

An ncurses video manager. VideoCrumb keeps track of the shows you watch so
you don't have to.

Currently it has the bare minimum level of, mostly hardcoded, functionality.
Written in C++ and using some C++0x features. See the github wiki for a
feature roadmap.

Dependencies:
	ncurses
	boost
		filesystem
		program_options

Tested with (x86_64):
  gcc 4.6
	GNU make 3.82
  boost 1.46
  ncurses 5.9

Compilation:
	$ make

Known bugs:
	Reading # of times a show has been watched from database always gives 0

Usage:
	./videocrumb

Controls:
	On any window, press ':' to enter command mode (like vim)
	Shows:
		<return>: add a new playlist
		<right arrow>: view selected playlist
	Playlist:
		<return>: add a new show
		<right arrow>, p: play selected show
	Settings:
